<!--{* 5. Section Features *}-->

<div class="section-features">
<div class="inner-wrapper">
 <span class="manually-placed-anchor" id="security"></span>
 <h2>Fully Featured with Advanced Security Components</h2>
 
 <div class="item-row item-row-3">
 <div class="live-mode">
  <a class="image" href="/wiki/Host_Live_Mode" target="_blank" title="Live Mode" style="background-image:url('/w/images/thumb/6/6a/Grub-persistent_mode_indicator_in_kicksecure.cleaned.png/800px-Grub-persistent_mode_indicator_in_kicksecure.cleaned.png');"></a>
  <h4>Live Mode</h4>
  <p>
   Booting into
   <a href="/wiki/Host_Live_Mode" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VM Live Mode</a>
   is as simple as choosing Live Mode in the boot menu.
  </p>
 </div>
  
 <div>
  <a class="image image-cover" href="/wiki/Time_Attacks" target="_blank" style="background-image:url('/w/images/thumb/0/04/Carriage-clock-797833640.jpg/240px-Carriage-clock-797833640.jpg');" title="Time"></a>
  <h4>Time Attack Defenses</h4>
  <p>
   <a href="/wiki/Time_Attacks" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Time attacks</a> are defeated by
   <a href="/wiki/Boot_Clock_Randomization" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boot Clock Randomization</a>
   and secure network time synchronization
   through <a href="/wiki/sdwdate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sdwdate</a> (Secure Distributed Web Date).
  </p>
 </div>
   
 <div>
  <a class="image image-cover" href="https://github.com/Kicksecure/tirdad" target="_blank" style="background-image:url('/w/images/thumb/f/f0/Resized_tirdad2.jpg/240px-Resized_tirdad2.jpg');" title="tirdad"></a>
  <h4>TCP ISN CPU Information Leak Protection</h4>
  <p>
   Prevents TCP ISN based kernel side-channel attacks through <a href="https://github.com/Kicksecure/tirdad" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tirdad kernel module for random ISN generation</a>.
  </p>
 </div>
 
 <div>
  <a class="image" disabled="disabled" target="_blank" style="background-image:url('/w/images/thumb/8/82/Firewall-symbol.png/300px-Firewall-symbol.png');" title="Advanced Firewall"></a>
  <h4>Advanced Firewall</h4>
  <p>No open ports by default.</p>
 </div>
 
 <div>
  <a class="image image-cover" href="https://github.com/Kicksecure/security-misc" target="_blank" style="background-image:url('/w/images/thumb/d/d7/Franck-v-_E1PQXKUkMw-unsplash.jpg/241px-Franck-v-_E1PQXKUkMw-unsplash.jpg');" title="Brute Force Defense"></a>
  <h4>Brute force attack protection</h4>
  <p>
   Protect user accounts against brute force attacks
   <a href="https://github.com/Kicksecure/security-misc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">By using pam tally2</a>
   .
  </p>
 </div>
 
 <div>
  <a class="image" href="/wiki/Anbox" target="_blank" style="background-image:url('/w/images/1/1f/Anbox.jpg');" title="Anbox"></a>
  <h4>Android Support</h4>
  <p>
   Run Android applications using
   <a href="/wiki/Anbox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anbox</a> (outdated)</a>.
  </p>
 </div>not
  
 <div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed no-item">
 <h4>12 more amazing features →</h4>
